A Bill
2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 HOUSE BILL 1760
4
5 By: Representative Milligan
6 By: Senator J. Boyd
7
For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING APPLICATIONS FOR
10 THE ADJUSTMENT OF A PROPERTY ASSESSMENT; TO PROVIDE
11 THAT A COUNTY EQUALIZATION BOARD DOES NOT HAVE
12 JURISDICTION TO DETERMINE WHETHER PROPERTY QUALIFIES
13 FOR CERTAIN PROPERTY TAX RELIEF; TO PROVIDE FOR A
14 COUNTY COURT'S JURISDICTION TO CONSIDER CERTAIN
15 PETITIONS FOR AN ADJUSTMENT OF A PROPERTY ASSESSMENT;
16 AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
17
18
Subtitle
19
20 TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING THE
21 JURISDICTION TO CONSIDER CERTAIN
22 PETITIONS FOR THE ADJUSTMENT OF A
23 PROPERTY ASSESSMENT.
24
25 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
26
27 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 26-27-317(a)(3), concerning applications
28 for adjustment of a county assessor's assessment of property, is amended to
29 read as follows:
30 (3) The county equalization board does not have jurisdiction
31 over and shall not accept or consider a petition or letter under subdivision
32 (a)(1) of this section for the adjustment of the:
33 (A) County assessor's determination of a property's tax-
34 exempt status under Arkansas Constitution, Article 16, § 5(b);
35 (B) Valuation of agricultural land, pasture land, or
36 timberland derived by the guidelines and methods set forth by the Assessment
